                        <support>1 papyrus ; 11.5 x15.5 cm.</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">The letter is well preserved and its entire text can be understood, in spite of several small lacunas along its folds. Three edges of the papyrus are intact; it is very likely, as well, that only one line of text is missing at the bottom edge. This is indicated by the position of the center horizontal fold and by the fact that the last preserved line of text contains the beginning of an expected epistolary closing. In addition to the horizontal fold, the papyrus has six vertical folds from left to right, hence fourteen panels of equal dimensions.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
