                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The letter on the recto is c: chi, kappa, ypsilon, and epsilon often have an additional upper flourish, while omicron is usually smaller than the other lettersand raised. The hand resembles a number of texts written in what is often called a chancery style. This letter, in particular, '. . . extends to the reader the courtesy of immediate legibility as well as beauty." The verso of the second panel from right contains an address in tall letters which slant to the left: to Claudius Agenor from Xenophon.</p>
